To generate a table of contents automatically in a LATEX document, you can use the `\tableofcontents` command. This command is typically placed after the document class and package declarations, and before the beginning of the document body.
Here is an example of a simple LATEX document with an automatically generated table of contents:
```
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{utf8}
\usepackage{graphicx}
\usepackage{hyperref}
\title{Example Document}
\author{John Doe}
\date{}
\begin{document}
\maketitle
\tableofcontents
\newpage
\section{Introduction}
This is the introduction section.
\subsection{Subsection}
This is a subsection within the introduction section.
\newpage
\section{Methods}
