\end{document}
```
In this example, the `\tableofcontents` command is placed after the document title and author information, and before the document body. The sections and subsections are declared using the `\section` and `\subsection` commands, respectively. The `\newpage` command is used to ensure that each section starts on a new page.
When the document is compiled, LATEX will automatically generate a table of contents based on the declared sections and subsections. The table of contents will be placed at the point where the `\tableofcontents` command is declared. 
